This legacy cursorrules file predates the .mdc format and is plain markdown
with no frontmatter at all. It should be split at each H2 heading into its own
memory so that individually addressable sections survive re-import cleanly and
the overview preamble becomes its own anchored chunk when it is long enough.

## Formatting Conventions

Always run the formatter before committing. Two-space indentation everywhere,
trailing commas in multi-line literals, and no unused imports. Keep lines under
one hundred columns wide so that side-by-side diffs stay readable. This section
is padded well beyond the fragment-fold threshold so it survives as its own fact.

## Testing Policy

Every feature needs both a unit test and an integration test. Prefer table
driven tests where practical, and never mock the thing under test. This section
is deliberately verbose so that it clears the two-hundred character minimum and
does not fold forward into a neighboring section during heading based chunking.
